cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use fastCDS in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "fastCDS: map protein-domain amino-acid coordinates to genomic exon/intron structure at proteome scale"
abstract: >
  fastCDS is a C++17 + Python tool that converts protein-domain
  amino-acid ranges (from InterProScan, HMMER/Pfam, UniProt features,
  or any BED-like input) into exact genomic coordinates, exon/intron
  decomposition, and plot-ready isoform structure tables. It is
  validated against ensembldb to 100 % exact match on a 5,000-query
  stratified set and runs ~900× faster than ensembldb at proteome
  scale.
